Summary

  • Weekly Win: Kevin Harts Facebook share of a Rally photo reached over 1.6m people, drove 30,000 likes/comments/shares, and resulted in 150 new page likes.
  • Channel Analysis: There was an issue with Facebook ad budgeting that caused a temporary drop in email captures. The Edelman team is correcting. Overall, Facebook is still the most cost-effective channel. The average cost-per-registration on Facebook this week was $0.78 (compared to an overall average of $1.1). The average cost-per-registration on Twitter this week was $12.46 (compared to an overall average of $62.47).
  • Targeting: Were continuing to target Kevin Hart fans. Waiting for UHC data on Rally eligibility before we ramp up state-specific targeting.
  • Email Campaigns: The emails continue to do fairly well. Holding off on Email 3 until we get additional assets, which we are pushing for.
